.TH TETHER 1 "@BUILD_DATE@" "Tether @TETHER_VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tether \- Wayland companion CLI for iPhone integration
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tether
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tether
is a command-line interface for communicating with the Tether daemon (\fBtetherd\fR).
It allows for clipboard synchronization, file transfers, and device management between
a Linux Wayland desktop and an iOS device.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h, \-\-help\fR
Show help message and exit.
.TP
\fB\-g, \-\-get-clipboard\fR
Retrieve the current Wayland clipboard text from the daemon.
.TP
\fB\-s, \-\-set-clipboard\fR [\fISTRING\fR]
Copy the provided string (or stdin if omitted) to the local Wayland clipboard.
.TP
\fB\-f, \-\-send-file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Send a file to the currently connected device.
.TP
\fB\-n, \-\-native-host\fR
Start the browser Native Messaging Host proxy loop (used by browser extensions).
.TP
\fB\-d, \-\-discover\fR
Scan the local network for tetherd instances via mDNS.
.TP
\fB\-\-host\fR \fIIP\fR
Connect over TCP to the daemon at the specified IP address instead of using the local UNIX socket.
.TP
\fB\-\-port\fR \fINUM\fR
Connect over TCP port (default: 5134).
.TP
\fB\-\-timeout\fR \fIMS\fR
Discovery scan duration in milliseconds (default: 3000).
.TP
\fB\-\-list-devices\fR
List all paired connection devices and their fingerprints.
.TP
\fB\-\-accept\fR \fIFINGERPRINT\fR
Accept a pending pairing request locally for the specified device fingerprint.
.TP
\fB\-\-pair\fR
Send a pairing request over TCP to the daemon.
.SH EXAMPLES
Retrieve clipboard:
.IP
tether \-g
.PP
Copy text to clipboard:
.IP
echo "Hello from Linux" | tether \-s
.PP
Discover other Tether instances:
.IP
tether \-\-discover
.PP
Send a file:
.IP
tether \-f document.pdf
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR tetherd (8),
.BR tether-gtk (1)
